<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-03-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-03-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="967" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d967">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Sultan of Turkey</gloss> to
                                President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Yildiz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-03-25"><hi rend="italic">March 25,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Very much touched by the felicitations you have been so good as to
                            express to me on the occasion of the Bairam. I return especial
                            thanks.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Abdul Hamid.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>